<subSubSection pageId="13" pageNumber="14" type="etymology">
<paragraph blockId="13.[151,1437,151,418]" box="[198,1351,271,298]" pageId="13" pageNumber="14">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[198,331,271,297]" pageId="13" pageNumber="14">Etymology</emphasis>
. Latin 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Yoshitomi &amp; Ruta" authorityYear="2010" box="[415,617,272,297]" class="Insecta" family="Scirtidae" genus="Scirtes" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="13" pageNumber="14" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="septemmaculatus">
<emphasis box="[415,617,272,297]" italics="true" pageId="13" pageNumber="14">septemmaculatus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
= with seven spots, refering to 7 yellow spots on each elytron.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="13.[151,1437,151,418]" pageId="13" pageNumber="14">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[198,275,311,337]" pageId="13" pageNumber="14">Notes.</emphasis>
Similar to 
<taxonomicName authority="Champion" authorityName="Champion, B" authorityYear="1918" box="[412,787,312,338]" class="Insecta" family="Scirtidae" genus="Scirtes" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="13" pageNumber="14" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="flavoguttatus">
<emphasis box="[412,653,312,337]" italics="true" pageId="13" pageNumber="14">Scirtes flavoguttatus</emphasis>
Champion
</taxonomicName>
, but elytra are dark brown (not black) and yellow pattern is not so contrasting. Parameres of subequal lengths in 
<taxonomicName authority="Champion" authorityName="Champion, B" authorityYear="1918" box="[848,1162,352,378]" class="Insecta" family="Scirtidae" genus="Scirtes" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="13" pageNumber="14" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="flavoguttatus">
<emphasis box="[848,1030,352,377]" italics="true" pageId="13" pageNumber="14">S. flavoguttatus</emphasis>
Champion
</taxonomicName>
, in 
<taxonomicName authority="Yoshitomi &amp; Ruta, 2010" authorityName="Yoshitomi &amp; Ruta" authorityYear="2010" box="[1205,1436,352,377]" class="Insecta" family="Scirtidae" genus="Scirtes" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="13" pageNumber="14" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="septemmaculatus" status="sp. n.">
<emphasis box="[1205,1436,352,377]" italics="true" pageId="13" pageNumber="14">S. septemmaculatus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<taxonomicNameLabel box="[151,213,392,418]" pageId="13" pageNumber="14" rank="species">sp. n.</taxonomicNameLabel>
one paramere is much longer.
</paragraph>
